
--->DOM(Document Object Model)
		--It is a programming interface in web development 
		  that allows us to interact and manipulate(change) the HTML documents.
		--When the webpage is loaded, the browser creates the DOM of the webpages.
		--When an html file loaded into the browser the javascript cannot understand the the html document dirctly.
		--DOM is basically the representation of the same document but in the form of tree-like structure 
		  composted of  different objects.Each node represents the attributes
		--HTML dom it allows javascript to access (get) and modify all the elements in HTML document. 

		
--->KEYPOINTS:-
---------------
				1)Structure:		The DOM represents the sturucture of HTML document as a tree;
				    		 		Each node in a tree represents the elements,attributes, text
				2)Manipulation:		Using js, you can interact with elements(buttons, h ,p) we can modify , add , remove elements
									change the styles.

----<In DOM the HTML elemsts are called as objects	
----<properity:-is a value that we can set to the objects(like changing content of the html element)
----<Methods:An action(like adding or deleting)

--->Methods Of DOM:-
		1)Getting an element methods:-
				*Getting an element by ID[id-targeted for single element]
				*Getting an element by Class[class-group of id's together]
					--Returns all the element having that
				*Getting an element by Tagnames
				*Getting an element by query selector
				<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="a">aa</h1>
    <h1 class="a">bb</h1>
    <h1 class="a">cc</h1>
    <h1 class="b">dd</h1>
    <h1 class="b">ee</h1>
    <h1 class="b">ff</h1>
    <h1 class="c">gg</h1>
    <h1 class="c">hh</h1>
    <h1 class="c">ii</h1>
    <script>
        let a=document.getElementsByClassName("a")
        console.log(a)
        for(let i=0;i<a.lenght;i++){
            console.log(a[i])
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
